President Obama has nominated Judge William K. Sessions III to be the Chair of the United States Sentencing Commission. Currently serving as a Vice Chair of the Commission, Judge Sessions has been a member since 1999, when he was nominated by President Clinton and confirmed by the Senate. He was re-nominated by President Bush for a second term in 2003. Judge Sessions has been a federal judge on the District Court of Vermont since 1995 and is a member of the Judicial Conference of the United States. He holds a bachelor's degree from Middlebury College and a J.D. from the National Law Center at George Washington University.